---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const updated = "June 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Pumkin"
  description="How Pumkin (Software For Humans) handles your data: what we collect, why, who processes it, and your rights."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="container legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      Pumkin is a product of <strong>Software For Humans</strong>, operated by Lewis LaBrie
      ("we", "us"). This policy explains what personal data we collect when you visit
      <a href="https://pumkin.app">pumkin.app</a> or buy a Pumkin license, why we collect it,
      who processes it, and the rights you have over it. Questions:
      <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      The Pumkin desktop app runs entirely on your machine. Your prompts, your models, your
      files, and your agent runs never reach us — there is no Pumkin cloud and no telemetry on
      your agent activity. The only personal data we hold is what's needed to sell you a license
      and deliver your download: your email, name, and payment confirmation.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Purchase information.</strong> When you buy a license, we receive your email
        address, name (if provided), and details of the transaction (amount, currency, a Stripe
        payment/session reference, and your founding-member number). We do <em>not</em> receive
        or store your full card number — payment card data is handled entirely by Stripe.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Download activity.</strong> We generate a unique download token tied to your
        purchase and record how many times it's used, so we can deliver and re-deliver your
        installer.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Email correspondence.</strong> If you email us for support, we keep that
        correspondence to help you.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Basic server logs.</strong> Our hosting provider may process standard technical
        data (such as IP address and request metadata) to serve the site securely. We do not use
        this for tracking or advertising.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do NOT do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not run advertising or third-party tracking pixels on this site.</li>
      <li>We do not collect any data from inside the Pumkin desktop application.</li>
      <li>We do not sell or rent your personal data to anyone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why we process it (legal bases)</h2>
    <p>
      We process your purchase and download data to <strong>perform our contract</strong> with
      you (selling and delivering the license). We process support emails and keep transaction
      records under our <strong>legitimate interests</strong> in running the business and our
      <strong>legal obligations</strong> (such as tax and accounting record-keeping).
    </p>

    <h2>Who processes your data</h2>
    <p>We use a small number of trusted service providers ("processors") to operate:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing.</li>
      <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — database storing your order record (hosted in the EU, Frankfurt region).</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — sending your welcome/download email.</li>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — website hosting.</li>
      <li><strong>DigitalOcean</strong> — storage and delivery of the installer file.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each operates under its own privacy terms. Some may process data outside your country; where
      that happens, appropriate safeguards (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) apply.
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your order record for as long as you hold a license and as long as required for
      legal and accounting purposes, then delete or anonymize it. You can ask us to delete your
      data sooner (subject to record-keeping obligations) — see below.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on where you live (including under the EU/UK GDPR), you have the right to access,
      correct, delete, or export your personal data, and to object to or restrict certain
      processing. To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>
      and we'll respond within a reasonable time. You also have the right to complain to your local
      data protection authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Pumkin is a developer tool intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect data from children.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the
      "last updated" date above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Software For Humans — Vigo, Spain. Email <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-nav"><a href="/terms">Terms of Service →</a></p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; padding-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal .updated { color: var(--brand-fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 2.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { line-height: 1.7; color: var(--brand-fg); }
  .legal p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .legal ul { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; padding-left: 1.4rem; }
  .legal li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--brand-accent-quiet); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal-nav { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--brand-border); }
</style>
